3 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 63 O.S. 2021, Section 3205, is
4 amended to read as follows:
5 Section 3205. A. The transfer of the University Hospitals from
6 the Commission for Human Services and the Department of Human
7 Services shall not require a Certificate of Need pursuant to the
8 provisions of Sections 2651 through 2656.2 of Title 63 of the
9 Oklahoma Statutes; provided, however, that Notwithstanding any other
10 law, any expansion, addition, or change to the University Hospitals
11 requiring a Certificate of Need after such transfer shall be subject
12 to the provisions of Sections 2651 through 2656.2 of Title 63 of the
13 Oklahoma Statutes in furtherance of the University Hospitals
14 Authority Act shall not require a certificate of need.
15 B. 1. University Hospitals shall be operated as general
16 hospitals and shall be licensed by the State Commissioner of Health,
17 and shall, as far as possible, meet the standards, requirements and
18 essentials of the Joint Commission on Accreditation of Health Care
19 Organizations, the American Medical Association’s Council on Medical
20 Education, the American Specialty Boards and the Association of
21 American Medical Colleges.
22 2. The University Hospitals shall operate a public Level I
23 Trauma Center and shall meet the standards and requirements of the
24 American College of Surgeons to attain such designation. The
ENGR. S. B. NO. 873 Page 7

1 Univ ersity Hospitals Authority shall annually certify to the
2 Oklahoma Health Care Authority that the University Hospitals meet
3 such standards and requirements with respect to any Medicaid
4 supplemental payments to be received from the Oklahoma Health Care
5 Authority for the public Level I Trauma Center.
6 3. The University Hospitals may provide services and receive
7 payments therefor under Titles XVIII and XIX of the federal Social
8 Security Act, and may participate in other federal medical programs.
9 3. 4. University Hospitals shall be available as teaching and
10 training hospitals for the colleges of the University of Oklahoma
11 Health Sciences Center, for the College of Medicine of the
12 University of Oklahoma College of Medicine, and for other health and
13 educational facilities and shall provide indigent patient care.
14 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
